//
//      ASL
//
//      some DEMOS and apps - written in asl
//
//      change to a directory -- find a file  xxx.asl
//      execute via   asl xxx.asl
//
//      apps that use the xgs GUI
//      are run  with asl -X xxx.asl
//      but optionally the app itself can launch the xgs GUI
//
//      a manual  ASLMAN.txt is located in DOCS directory
//      nroff ASLMAN.txt   will produce a formated document.
//
//      the sinfo command will give info on library functions
//      e.g sinfo scut
//      gives :-
//
//     scut()
//     ws=scut(w1,nc)
//     cuts n chars from head or tail ( if n is negative) of the string w1,
//     and returns result to string ws.
//
//     a sorted list of known functions can be obtained via
//
//     asl -s 'S=functions(); S->sort(); <<" %(1,\t,,,\n)$S\n"'
//
//     each function  has  a brief one line description.
//     extended information can be obtained via sinfo
//     and via the manual.
//
//
//     example scripts for many of the functions can be found
//     in the TESTS/ITOCS/ directory usually in a directory of the
//     the same name. (TEST/ITOC/Scut,  TEST/ITOC/Scat, ...).
//     Usually the example script shows most options and tests of
//     the function.
//
//     Examples of asl syntax are also in the TEST/ITOC directory
//     (e.g. While, If). 
//
//      In the gapps directory - where this package was installed
//      DEMOS has some examples of applications that can be
//      built, and the  TEST/XASL/ShmIPC directory 
//      has a number   of example scripts of using asl with the Xwindow app xgs.
//


//  will be adding str and chr class to take care of wchar, char options
